description:
Data was extracted from the TARGET program in April 2017. This clinical information about patient cases was generated from a set of XLSX files downloaded from https://target-data.nci.nih.gov/Public/.../clinical/harmonized. More details: see https://ocg.cancer.gov/programs/target. 

NOTE: While this table contains information about over 5000 TARGET cases, this does not necessarily mean that molecular data exists for all of them, nor that the NCI GDC data repository currently contains all available data. Cases are grouped into projects. In general, each project is associated with a single disease, although ALL (Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia) has two projects: Phase1 and Phase2 (P1 and P2). Some fields in this table may be relevant to only one of the sub-projects and will therefore be null for many of the cases. The fields are (approximately) ordered from left to right where the fields towards the left are rarely null, while the fields toward the right are almost always null.

fields.description: Each row of this table describes a unique TARGET  case (participant), identified by a barcode such as TARGET-52-PAWFWK
fields.name: case_barcode

fields.description: GDC unique identifier for this case (corresponds to the case_barcode)  --  this can be used to access more information from the GDC data portal like this:   https://portal.gdc.cancer.gov/files/c21b332c-06c6-4403-9032-f91c8f407ba9
fields.name: case_gdc_id

fields.description: Program Name, always TARGET (Therapeutically Applicable Research To Generate Effective Treatments) in this table.
fields.name: program_name

fields.description: Program dbGaP accession number, eg phs000178
fields.name: program_dbgap_accession_number

fields.description: Project name abbreviation; the TARGET program is composed of multiple projects, with abbreviations such as TARGET-ALL-P2, TARGET-AML, TARGET-WT, etc.
fields.name: project_short_name

fields.description: Project Name; frequently the same as or similar to the project disease type eg   Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia - Phase II   or   Breast Invasive Carcinoma   etc
fields.name: project_name

fields.description: A code representing the type of cancer. Values can be found at https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-TCGA-users/TCGA-code-tables/TCGA-study-abbreviations; eg. OV, GBM, LUAD
fields.name: disease_code

fields.description: Participant gender; e.g. Male, Female
fields.name: gender

fields.description: Survival state of the participant; e.g. dead, alive
fields.name: vital_status

fields.description: The race of a participant, independent from ethnicity; e.g. White, Black or African American, Asian, Native Hawaiian or other Pacific Islander, American Indian or Alaska Native
fields.name: race

fields.description: The ethnic origination of a participant, independent from race; e.g. Not Hispanic or Latino, Hispanic or Latino
fields.name: ethnicity

fields.description: Age, in years, at which a condition or disease was first diagnosed
fields.name: age_at_diagnosis

fields.description: Days since birth (a negative value, relative to the date of diagnosis which is considered to be t=0)
fields.name: days_to_birth

fields.description: If vital_status indicates 'alive', then this is the number of days from the date of diagnosis to the last followup (communication contact).
fields.name: days_to_last_followup

fields.description: Number of days from the date of diagnosis to the last day on which a person was known to be alive. This field is a combination of the days_to_last_followup and days_to death fields. Therefore, this field can be used whether the vital_status is 'alive' or 'dead'.
fields.name: days_to_last_known_alive

fields.description: If vital_status indicates 'dead', then this is the number of days to death (a positive value) relative to the date of diagnosis.
fields.name: days_to_death

fields.description: Alphanumeric code of the protocol(s); can be a comma-delimited string, but generally just a single protocol is specified; eg. AALL0232, etc.
fields.name: protocol

fields.description: Four digit year of the diagnosis
fields.name: year_of_diagnosis

fields.description: The year of the last followup (communication contact); eg. 2014.
fields.name: year_of_last_follow_up

fields.description: Number of days between the end of primary treatment for a cancer and the first event (complication, recurrence, etc)
fields.name: event_free_survival_time_in_days

fields.description: Type of the first disease event; eg. Death, Relapse, Progresssion, Induction failure, etc.
fields.name: first_event

fields.description: White Blood Cell count at diagnosis
fields.name: WBC_at_diagnosis

fields.description: Presence or absence of abnormalities in the Mixed Lineage Leukemia (MLL) gene; eg. positive, negative
fields.name: MLL_status

fields.description: Indicator of Central Nervous System site of relapse or induction failure; eg. yes, no
fields.name: CNS_site_of_relapse_or_induction_failure

fields.description: Indicates classification of presence of Central Nervous System (CNS) disease at diagnosis ( https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2990693/ ); eg. CNS 1, CNS 2, or CNS 3 (or null)
fields.name: CNS_status_at_diagnosis

fields.description: Bone marrow site of relapse or induction failure
fields.name: bone_marrow_site_of_relapse_or_induction_failure

fields.description: Indicator of other site of relapse or induction failure; eg. yes, no, null
fields.name: other_site_of_relapse_or_induction_failure

fields.description: Histology information; eg. Unfavorable, FHWT, DAWT, etc.
fields.name: histology

fields.description: Presence or absence of BCR-ABL1 fusion (aka Philadelphia Chromosome); eg. positive, negative, or null
fields.name: BCR_ABL1_status

fields.description: Bone Marrow Aspiration (BMA) blast count on day 8
fields.name: BMA_blasts_day_8

fields.description: Bone Marrow Aspiration (BMA) blast count on day 15
fields.name: BMA_blasts_day_15

fields.description: Bone Marrow Aspiration (BMA) blast count on day 29
fields.name: BMA_blasts_day_29

fields.description: Bone Marrow Aspiration (BMA) blast count on day 43
fields.name: BMA_blasts_day_43

fields.description: The DNA index (DI, or ratio of the DNA content of leukemic v normal G0/G1 cells); a prognostic factor in childhood acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL)
fields.name: DNA_index

fields.description: Indicates whether the participant has Down syndrome; eg. Yes, No
fields.name: Down_syndrome

fields.description: Minimal Residual Disease (MRD) at end of course 1; a percentage value
fields.name: MRD_at_end_of_course_1

fields.description: MRD at end of course 1; eg. yes or no (anything above 0.10 % is called yes)
fields.name: MRD_at_end_of_course_1_YN

fields.description: Minimal Residual Disease (MRD) at end of course 2; a percentage value
fields.name: MRD_at_end_of_course_2

fields.description: MRD at end of course 2; eg. yes or no (anything above 0.10 % is called yes)
fields.name: MRD_at_end_of_course_2_YN

fields.description: Minimal Residual Disease (MRD) at day 8 (percentage)
fields.name: MRD_day_8

fields.description: Minimal Residual Disease (MRD) at day 29 (percentage)
fields.name: MRD_day_29

fields.description: Minimal Residual Disease (MRD) at day 43 (percentage)
fields.name: MRD_day_43

fields.description: Minimal Residual Disease (MRD) at end of consolidation (ie at end of treatment)
fields.name: MRD_end_consolidation

fields.description: Cell type of origin; eg. B precursor, T-Cell, Indeterminate
fields.name: cell_of_origin

fields.description: Testes site of relapse; eg. yes, no or null
fields.name: testes_site_of_relapse

fields.description: Indicates whether cancer has spread from a tumor to the testis; eg. yes, no or null
fields.name: testicular_involvement

fields.description: Generally null, but may contain some useful information about a particular case
fields.name: comment

fields.description: Presence or absence of simultatenous trisomy of chromosomes 4 and 10.; eg. positive, negative or null
fields.name: trisomies_4_10_Status

fields.description: Status of ETV6-RUNX1 fusion; the most common genetic aberration in childhood ALL; eg.  positive, negative
fields.name: ETV6_RUNX1_fusion_status

fields.description: Eg. 46,XY[20]; for more details on what this means, see https://chromodisorder.org/introduction-to-chromosomes/
fields.name: karyotype

fields.description: TCF3-PBX1 fusion status; eg. negative, positive; see http://atlasgeneticsoncology.org/Anomalies/t0119ID1048.html
fields.name: TCF3_PBX1_status

fields.description: Children' s Oncology Group (COG) risk group; eg. High Risk, Low Risk and Intermediate Risk, see https://www.cancer.org/cancer/neuroblastoma/detection-diagnosis-staging/risk-groups.html
fields.name: COG_risk_group

fields.description: International Classification of Disease for Oncology (ICDO description); eg. Posterior mediastinum; see  https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Classification_of_Diseases_for_Oncology
fields.name: ICDO_description

fields.description: International Neuroblastoma Staging System (INSS) stage; values are Stage 1, Stage 2a, Stage 2b, Stage 3, Stage 4, and stage 4s
fields.name: INSS_stage

fields.description: MYCN Gene Amplification Status; eg. Amplified, Not Amplified, null
fields.name: MYCN_status

fields.description: International Classification of Disease of Oncology (ICDO) code; eg. C74.9
fields.name: ICDO

fields.description: The diagnostic category; eg. Neuroblastoma, Ganglioneuroblastoma, nodular, etc. (null for 80% of cases)
fields.name: diagnostic_category

fields.description: Value based on the DNA content of the tumor cell population compared to normal diploid cells based on flow cytometry; value between 1 and 5
fields.name: ploidy

fields.description: CCAAT Enhancer Binding Protein Alpha (CEBPA) mutation status; CEBPA is a transcription factor involved in the differentiation of certain blood cells; eg. yes, no
fields.name: CEBPA_mutation

fields.description: Indicates if Central Nervous System disease exists; eg. yes, no
fields.name: CNS_disease

fields.description: Complete Response status at end of treatment course 1; eg. CR, or Not in CR, (or more rarely Death or Unevaluable)
fields.name: CR_status_at_end_of_course_1

fields.description: Complete Response status at end of treatment course 2; eg. CR, or Not in CR, (or more rarely Death or Unevaluable)
fields.name: CR_status_at_end_of_course_2

fields.description: Indicator whether FLT3 Internal Tandem Duplication is positive; eg. yes, no or null
fields.name: FLT3_ITD_positive

fields.description: FLT3 Point Mutations; eg. yes, or null
fields.name: FLT3_PM

fields.description: International System for Cytogenetic Nomenclature (ISCN) code; eg. 45,XY[20]
fields.name: ISCN

fields.description: Mitosis-Karyorrhexis index: count of cells undergoing mitosis or karyorrhexis, based on count of 5000 cells; ether low (< 100 cells), intermediate (100-199 cells), or high (>=200 cells)
fields.name: MKI

fields.description: Nucelophosmin (NPM) gene mutation status; eg.  yes, no or null
fields.name: NPM_mutation

fields.description: Presence or absence of Wilms Tumor protein 1;a transcription factor necessary for the development of the kidneys and gonads; eg.  yes or no
fields.name: WT1_mutation

fields.description: Percentage of myeloblasts (blasts for short) in the bone marrow or blood; generally at least 20% is required for a diagnosis of AML
fields.name: bone_marrow_leukemic_blast_percentage

fields.description: Indicates if a chloroma exists; a chloroma is an extramedullary manifestation of acute myeloid leukemia; in other words, it is a solid collection of leukemic cells occurring outside of the bone marrow; eg. yes, no
fields.name: chloroma

fields.description: Number of unrelated cytogenetic abnormalities in a single karyotype; eg. values range from 0 to 10, also the string More than 6 occurs several times
fields.name: cytogenetic_complexity

fields.description: Indicates presence of 5q deletion syndrome; eg. yes, no
fields.name: del5q

fields.description: Indicates presence of 7q deletion syndrome; eg. yes, no
fields.name: del7q

fields.description: Indicates presence of 5q deletion syndrome; eg. yes, no
fields.name: del9q

fields.description: Tumor differentiation; eg. Differentiating, Undifferentiated or Poorly Differentiated
fields.name: grade

fields.description: Indicator of inv(16);  inv(16) is one of the most frequent chromosomal translocations associated with AML; eg. yes, no
fields.name: inv_16

fields.description: Loss of an X chromosome; eg. yes, no
fields.name: minus_X

fields.description: Loss of an Y chromosome; eg. yes, no
fields.name: minus_Y

fields.description: Loss of whole chromosome 5; eg. yes, no
fields.name: monosomy_5

fields.description: Loss of whole chromosome 7; eg. yes, no
fields.name: monosomy_7

fields.description: The percentage of blast (immature) cells in a sample of peripheral blood in a patient.
fields.name: peripheral_blasts_pct

fields.description: Primary cytogenetic code; eg. Other, Normal, MLL, t(8;21), inv(16) etc  (but null for 80% of cases)
fields.name: primary_cytogenetic_code

fields.description: This field may complement the previous COG_risk_group since they are never both defined for any one case; in this field the values Standard, Low, and High are observed the most frequently, with 10 (n=2) and 30 (n=1) also observed
fields.name: risk_group

fields.description: Indicates  t(10:11)(p11.2:q23) karyotype abnormality; eg. yes, no; see http://atlasgeneticsoncology.org/Anomalies/t1011ID1178.html
fields.name: t_10_11_p11_2_q23

fields.description: Represents the t(11:19)(q23:p13.1) karyotype abnormality; see http://atlasgeneticsoncology.org/Anomalies/t1119ELLID1029.html
fields.name: t_11_19_q23_p13_1

fields.description: Indicates t(3:5)(q25:q34) karyotype abnormality; eg. yes, no; see http://atlasgeneticsoncology.org/Anomalies/t0305ID1007.html
fields.name: t_3_5_q25_q34

fields.description: Indicates t(6:11)(q27:q23) karotype abnormality; eg. yes, no; see http://atlasgeneticsoncology.org/Anomalies/t0611ID1015.html
fields.name: t_6_11_q27_q23

fields.description: Indicates t(6:9) karyotype abnormality; eg. yes, no
fields.name: t_6_9

fields.description: Indicates t(8:21) karyotype abnormality; eg. yes, no
fields.name: t_8_21

fields.description: Indicates t(9:11)(p22:q23) karyotype abnormality; eg. yes, no; see http://atlasgeneticsoncology.org/Anomalies/t0911ID1001.html
fields.name: t_9_11_p22_q23

fields.description: Presence of three copies of chromosome 8; eg. yes, no
fields.name: trisomy_8

fields.description: Presence of three copies of chromosome 21; eg. yes, no
fields.name: trisomy_21

fields.description: French-American-British classification; values range from M0 to M7, with some NOS (also null for over 80% of cases)
fields.name: FAB_category

fields.description: Stem Cell Transplantation in first Complete Remission; eg. yes, no or null
fields.name: SCT_in_1st_CR

fields.description: Numeric value representing the percentage of a tumor in a sample or specimen; eg. 90
fields.name: percent_tumor

fields.description: Code that represents the histology (morphology) of the disease using the third edition of the International Classification of Diseases for Oncology, published in 2000; eg. 8960/3
fields.name: ICD_O_3_M

fields.description: Code that represents the site (topology) of the disease using the third edition of the International Classification of Diseases for Oncology, published in 2000; eg. C649
fields.name: ICD_O_3_T

fields.description: Cancer stage; eg. III  --  values observed include I, II, III, IV, and also IIIB, IIIB/V, III/IV, II/V, and III/V
fields.name: stage

fields.description: Indicates whether the disease is being discovered or validated; eg. discovery, validation or null
fields.name: discovery_or_validation

fields.description: Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia (ALL) molecular pathology subtype; eg. TCF3-PBX1, etc.
fields.name: ALL_mol_subtype

fields.description: Indicator of chloroma site of relapse or induction failure; eg. yes, no
fields.name: chloroma_site_of_relapse_or_induction_failure

fields.description: Indicator of cytogenetic site of relapse or induction failure; eg. yes, no
fields.name: cytogenetic_site_of_relapse_or_induction_failure

fields.description: Numeric value representing the percentage of necrosis in a sample or specimen.
fields.name: percent_necrosis

fields.description: Numeric representation of the ratio of tumor to stroma; eg. 40/60, 75/25
fields.name: percent_tumor_vs_stroma

fields.description: Site of relapse; eg. Primary site, etc.
fields.name: site_of_relapse

fields.description: Alternate therapy; eg. Chemotherapy, Transplant, Surgery, etc.
fields.name: alternate_therapy

fields.description: Indicator of c-kit mutation exon 8; eg. yes, no or null
fields.name: c_Kit_mutation_exon8

fields.description: Indicator of c-kit mutation exon 17; eg. yes, no or null
fields.name: c_Kit_mutation_exon17

fields.description: Cytogenetic code; eg. t(17;19)(q11.2;q13.3), etc.
fields.name: cytogenetic_code_other

fields.description: Indicates whether the disease was metastatic or non-metastatic at diagnosis; eg. Metastatic, Non-metastatic, Metastatic (confirmed), Non-metastatic (confirmed), Non-metastatic (unconfirmed)
fields.name: disease_at_diagnosis

fields.description: The location on the body where the primary tumor exists; eg. Arm/Hand, Pelvis, etc.
fields.name: primary_tumor_site

fields.description: Specific tumor site on the body; eg. Pelvis, Femur, etc.
fields.name: specific_tumor_site

fields.description: Time in days until the first event
fields.name: time_to_first_event_in_days

fields.description: FLT3 Internal Tandem Duplication Allele Ratio
fields.name: FLT3_ITD_allelic_ratio

fields.description: The type of definitive surgery; e.g. Amputation, Limb sparing, etc.
fields.name: definitive_surgery

fields.description: The histological response to an intervention; e.g. Good, Poor, Favorable
fields.name: histologic_response

fields.description: Reason for death; e.g. Tumor, Infection, Toxicity, etc.
fields.name: reason_for_death

fields.description: Specific tumor region on the body; e.g. Proximal, Distal
fields.name: specific_tumor_region

fields.description: Specific tumor side of the body; e.g. right, left
fields.name: specific_tumor_side

fields.description: Time in days to first relapse
fields.name: time_to_first_relapse_in_days

fields.description: Other alternate therapy; e.g. Bone marrow transplant, Palliative chemotherapy, etc.
fields.name: alternate_therapy_other

fields.description: Metastasis site; e.g. Bone, Lung only
fields.name: metastasis_site

fields.description: Indicates whether there has been progression at the primary site; eg. yes, no
fields.name: primary_site_progression

fields.description: Refractory timepoint sent for induction failure project; eg. EOI I, EOI II
fields.name: refractory_timepoint_sent_for_induction_failure_project

fields.description: Numeric value representing the percentage of cell death in a malignant tumor sample or specimen for the first relapse tissue.
fields.name: relapse_percent_necrosis

fields.description: Numeric representation of the percentage of tumor for the first sample of relapse tissue.
fields.name: relapse_percent_tumor

fields.description: Relapse type; e.g. Systemic, Locally recurrent
fields.name: relapse_type

fields.description: Type of therapy; e.g. Adria/Plat/MTX, etc.
fields.name: therapy

fields.description: Time in days from the date of enrollment to the date of initial secondary malignant neoplasm (SMN) diagnosis
fields.name: time_to_first_SMN_in_days

fields.description: Time in days to first enrollment on relapse protocol
fields.name: time_to_first_enrollment_on_relapse_protocol_in_days
